  "text": "For all values, indices based on pigments were underestimated by the drone imagery of higher SR due to the larger weight of ground-pixels when comparing to the airplane pictures with lower SR. The good relationship between TCARI/ OSAVI of the hyperspectral imagery and proximal sensors, reinforced the presence of the SR effect (Fig. 6 ). For instance, NBI was highly related with TCARI/OSAVI calculated from airborne sensors (R 2 ¼ 0.79) but not from drone measurements (R 2 ¼ 0.02). The practical importance of the SR effect might be mitigated in real situation fields were the probability of finding fields with yield losses >25% due to N deficiency is very low [CITATION_1] . Nevertheless, the effect of ground pixels may be relevant when airborne indices are used to identify responsive sites to N at topdressing at early development stages, when the LAI and ground cover is still low.",
